Video Session Configuration
  Input session configuration
    - Unicast (dest UDP) or Multicast (SSM)
    - input session id
  Output session configuration
    - QAM id, program id

RF Configuration
  The same RF configuration for DOCSIS will be used for RF configuration.


Data Structures:
  Unicast session map:
    64 K entries, one for each UPD port number.
    contains input session ID

  Multicast session map (hash table):
    key derived from source IP and dest group addresses
    contains input session ID
    (* To simplify data packet lookup, only one multicast mode (ASM or SSM)
       is supported!)

  Input session info:
    SPTS or MPTS
    status: off, configured, snooping, ready
    processing modes: PSI (on/off), clock recovery (on/off)


---------------------------------------
MB should not be encryption aware.

ECM is per program.  EMM are shared among all output programs.

ECM comes to MB inband with the program.
ECM PID is specified in the CA_descriptor in PMT.
So we do need to parse and regenerate CA_descriptor.

EMM PID needs to be inserted into the output stream.
EMM PID is specified in CAT.  Usually CAT does not appear in the input.
CAT table needs to be inserted into output PSI.
It should contain the EMM PID based on configuation.

